Program: Outlook
Title: Living With My Mother's Murder
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p054kky0
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 8 Jun 2017
Alex Hanscombe explains how he's overcome the trauma of seeing his mum, Rachel Nickell, murdered in front of him in a London park when he was two-years-old. Mandy Harvey is a deaf American jazz singer who's become an internet sensation. She grew up singing and was studying music when she lost her hearing. She explains how she was able to continue with her passion. Emtithal Mahmoud is a Sudanese-American performance poet whose work was inspired by the conflict in Darfur and the family she has living there. Image: Alex Hanscombe with his mother Rachel Nickell. Credit: Alex Hanscombe Show less